<mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#eeb3b3;strokeColor=#c0392b;fontColor=#5a1410;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="1131" y="1657" width="244" height="108" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Morality is not real&lt;br&gt;(anti-realism)&lt;br&gt;[1+3+4+7+8]&lt;br&gt;→ nothing — ranking flat&lt;br&gt;(J. L. Mackie)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + living_in_simulation + morality_is_not_real&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Off the end of the line: if moral realism is false there is no stance-independent reason to help anyone. Every DALY is set to 0 — the moral circle, welfare ranges, discounting and simulation probabilities all stop mattering, and the ranking goes flat. The consistent recommendation is to keep the money. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 3 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 4 no_discounting_future_humans → 7 living_in_simulation → 8 morality_is_not_real" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJyNVdtu20gM%2FRXC2MXagePIuaCpF36wY%2BWCdbdB6m6xiANlLFHWbEczwszIijbNv5cj%2BZo0gJ8si%2BQheXhIPTcijFku7IWKsNFrHB1Bv9%2BHiWZcglUQavZ%2FSQ%2BFhGl%2B7HVPoVBaRAuOBRTd4CQ4DT4E59A0VmVw3nLBU0kgA2PyNLNcSQgTwuqBBxnTKkw4Ew6q%2B%2FEYuhAzHbCClUGSp0yaleEE4tzmGpevg5RZizoouE2CiJtQ5dJyOV%2B5n4JU2%2B%2BDneiV1wcQfOGsXAaGp7lgVXlL6zmkSjPBbRlwE0hlA41MVL34LEyAbRriBhjcljah55gLBKJqYzZHYBNmgUWRaYNG4pdLNKB0BabxkHhgKVJD3NB7m2BN0R%2BGupZhhfEnhCrNlHFNrh0oVkZIiPSKmwrNWCYjJpREKj9C0YHH9Xz8xaMr1YXjU4ahpcAFEzmCiiuEzSg7FdgQjYVZXkLu0rhAg9uN9Yhmiqt5d1LQTH53f2Oisoa48v%2F27wYTfwSzEuYoUTOLnaxcRWDE7Q5XB2RsO9y6IkcnIVVYI66paMA4dj%2FENbo5KD0nojLNU6ZLmFGKmIecntsw9C8%2F3%2Fn1HCuEAvk8cYIgWoRyck74Yz0%2BoeZS6ZS0%2BNH7HS5uoKk0NX2o4sOUzSW3eYQw%2FDzxL1pUj1F59he3YYJyxER5i%2FqriaAPz1MJkKHKBF6jyDBaW7yOd%2BYSep0z51OgEDOkSq5ojg6idvG6tY%2FXdU6VfFHHLLQ5E0Mi959qXM715J1MB7%2BAPoBmFw7fg2tN5ctUzqOdRlwty3q946lkafzafFxbqVDG0zex3bXVJmLHWllOPOKwyHYNnrOceR7ZCi6iWT43Ow